nt":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"---\n##  Section 18 — Summary & Conclusions\n\n###  What We Built\n\n| Engine | Method | Best Use Case |\n|--------|--------|---------------|\n| **Engine 1** — Plot-Based | TF-IDF on Overview + Cosine Similarity | User wants movies with similar storylines |\n| **Engine 2** — Genre-Based | CountVectorizer on Genre Tags | User wants movies in same genre categories |\n| **Engine 3** — Hybrid | TF-IDF on (Genre × 2 + Overview + Language) | Best overall — balances plot + genre |\n| **Bonus** — Top Charts | IMDB Bayesian Weighted Rating | Discover high-quality titles objectively |\n\n###  Key Findings\n\n- **Engine 3 (Hybrid)** consistently achieves the highest genre overlap score across test movies\n- **Engine 2 (Genre-Only)** has perfect genre overlap but sometimes sacrifices plot relevance\n- **Engine 1 (Plot-Only)** captures thematic similarity better but may cross genre boundaries\n- The **IMDB Weighted Rating** is a fairer ranking than raw `Vote_Average` alone\n- Most movies cluster in the **0.6–0.7 rating** band, making differentiation important\n\n###  Limitations\n\n- **No user data** — this is content-based only; cannot do collaborative filtering\n- **Cold start** problem — new titles with sparse data may not recommend well\n- **Language bias** — English overviews dominate TF-IDF space (~77% of dataset)\n- **Popularity ≠ Quality** — high-popularity titles don't always get the best recommendations\n\n###  Future Improvements\n\n- [ ] Add **Collaborative Filtering** using user ratings (SVD, ALS)\n- [ ] Use **BERT / Sentence Transformers** for semantic plot embeddings\n- [ ] Build a **Streamlit web app** with live search and poster display\n- [ ] Add **actor / director** features to improve recommendation quality\n- [ ] Implement **Matrix Factorization** (SVD++) for hybrid collaborative\n- [ ] Deploy as a **Kaggle Inference notebook** with widgets","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"print('=' * 60)\nprint('   🎬 